through the evocation of a quasi-sadistic pessimism, then in the embodiment of the "sun-god of Art," and, finally, as a feeble gesture toward an unknowable deity which moves elusively both within and beyond the natural world. Rather than imposing artificial unity on the poet's career, Louis presents his work as an integrated series of serious and brilliant experiments in Romantic art.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aLord's Supper in literature. 0aRomanticism. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978077356214140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780773562141423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780773562141/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles